## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Navigation Architecture Change**: The current `SearchScreen` is a bottom tab screen. This plan converts the tab's `Search` to navigate directly to a new **dedicated `SearchScreen`** (full-screen stack screen) when tapped. The bottom tab "Search" will become a lightweight gateway that immediately pushes the real search experience. This is how apps like Airbnb, OLX, and Swiggy handle search UX.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **New Dependencies**: This plan requires `react-native-reanimated` (already installed v4.1.1), `react-native-gesture-handler` (already installed v2.28.0), `expo-haptics` (already installed), and `@react-native-async-storage/async-storage` (NEW — needed for persisting recent searches). No other new packages are needed.

> [!WARNING]  
> **Backend Addition**: A new lightweight `/api/v1/pg/suggestions` endpoint is proposed for real-time search suggestions (returns PG names + areas matching a prefix). This is a read-only endpoint and doesn't affect existing APIs.

